# Goblins OS — operator secret provisioning (server-side only).
#
# This file is the operator-provisioning home for OpenAI service credentials. On
# the image it is mode 0600 root:root: readable by root alone. systemd (PID 1)
# copies it into goblins-os-core's private runtime credential directory with
# LoadCredential; it is never exported into the core process environment. The
# same runtime read path accepts a LoadCredentialEncrypted drop-in, after systemd
# decrypts and authenticates that payload. The persistent resident heartbeat,
# auto-login desktop user, its group, and the GUI session can NEVER read it. It is
# NEVER sourced into the desktop session. The immutable image ships it empty — no
# credentials are baked in. An operator (or enterprise MDM/enrollment) supplies
# the values below via a managed copy of this file or a per-service systemd
# credential drop-in. Use literal UTF-8 NAME=VALUE lines; matching outer quotes
# are accepted, but shell expansion is intentionally unsupported. The
# native clients receive only readiness and plain-language storage labels, never
# tokens or credential paths. Codex login is stored separately in owner-only OS
# state. A bring-your-own API key is accepted only here, inside the protected
# service credential; no desktop process accepts or transports it.
#
# Real OpenAI account login -- OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code + PKCE, run entirely
# by the OS core on loopback. Register the redirect URI with the OAuth client.
#OPENAI_ACCOUNT_AUTH_URL=https://<openai-oauth-issuer>/authorize
#OPENAI_ACCOUNT_TOKEN_URL=https://<openai-oauth-issuer>/oauth/token
#OPENAI_ACCOUNT_CLIENT_ID=<openai-oauth-client-id>
#OPENAI_ACCOUNT_CLIENT_SECRET=<only-for-confidential-clients>
#OPENAI_ACCOUNT_REDIRECT_URI=http://127.0.0.1:8787/v1/auth/openai/callback
#OPENAI_ACCOUNT_SCOPE=openid profile email offline_access
# Optional browserless OS login: OAuth 2.0 Device Authorization Grant (RFC 8628).
# The login gate shows a short user code + verification URL and polls for the token.
#OPENAI_ACCOUNT_DEVICE_AUTH_URL=https://<openai-oauth-issuer>/oauth/device/code
#
# Persistent Goblins AI runtime routes. A configured route is never an implicit
# fallback: the user or administrator must explicitly select its named engine.
# Choose either or both as policy permits:
# Older deployment-specific aliases are accepted by OS services for existing
# deployments, but the shipping image publishes only Goblins-native keys.
#   (a) direct OpenAI Responses API (`openai-api`; billed to this key)
#OPENAI_API_KEY=<server-side-only-openai-api-key>
#   (b) managed OpenAI relay (`cloud-openai`; prompts leave the device)
#GOBLINS_OS_RESIDENT_RELAY_URL=https://<relay-host>/goblins-os
#AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=<server-side-only-gateway-key>
#   (c) local-only GPT-OSS adapter (`local-gpt-oss`; no credentials at all)
#GOBLINS_OS_LOCAL_MODEL_RELAY=http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1/resident
#
# Optional official OpenAI SDK/service bridges. These are HTTPS server-side
# relays; the SDK runtime and OpenAI credentials live on the relay or in OS
# services, never in the desktop session or app clients. The Agents SDK bridge is
# a separate explicit service; it never overrides Build Studio's selected engine.
#GOBLINS_OS_AGENTS_SDK_RELAY_URL=https://<relay-host>/agents
#GOBLINS_OS_REALTIME_RELAY_URL=https://<relay-host>/realtime
#GOBLINS_OS_IMAGES_RELAY_URL=https://<relay-host>/images
#GOBLINS_OS_CHATKIT_RELAY_URL=https://<relay-host>/chatkit
#
# Signed local-model manifests are placed in GOBLINS_OS_MODEL_MANIFEST_DIR by the
# OS-owned model service; weights are SHA-256 verified at install and are never
# bundled in the immutable image.
